 Updated User Guide:

1. Open your web browser and navigate to https://signup.live.com/ or visit www.outlook.com by clicking on "Sign Up" in the top right corner of the screen.
2. Enter your preferred email address in the sign-up form, ensuring it is unique and easy to remember. Create a strong password that includes uppercase and lowercase letters, numbers, and symbols for added security. Confirm your chosen password by re-entering it in the "Confirm Password" field.
3. Fill out personal information: First name, Last name, Country or region, Birthdate, and Gender. This data is used for account recovery purposes if needed.
4. Choose a security question from the available options and enter your answer in the "Security Information" field to aid in identity verification.
5. Review Microsoft Services & Software License Agreement, Terms of Use, Privacy Statement, and Copyright Disclaimer. If you agree with these terms, select "I have read and agree to the privacy statement."
6. Click on the "Create Account" button located at the bottom right corner of the page to create your new Microsoft Outlook account using the provided information.
7. You will be redirected to a welcome screen where you can start setting up your email account by adding contacts, configuring settings, and more through the web interface at www.outlook.com or an email client with POP3/IMAP access.
8. If prompted during sign-up, follow any additional steps required for two-factor authentication or other security measures to protect your account from unauthorized access.